    "body": "> I see why it's not in payload, since that would cause the default implementation to need to strip them, but I kinda feel like it fits better under payload or metadata than as top-level key\r\n\r\nyou're right. `attribute` could probably be there as a top-level key, but `hits` doesn't really fit much. Do you think it makes sense to have a key like `metadata` and have `attribute` or `hits` under it?",
